1905	\section{Out of scope}
1906	\label{sec:gr_out_of_scope}
1907	
1908	This chapter constructs the Grassmannian \emph{scheme} \(\mathrm{Gr}(r,d)\) over
1909	the absolute base \(\mathbb{Z}\) and establishes its smoothness, separatedness
1910	and properness. The following constructions are deferred to later chapters and
1911	are not treated here:
1912	\begin{itemize}
1913	  \item \textbf{The tautological/universal quotient} \(u : \mathcal{O}^{\oplus
1914	    r}_{\mathrm{Gr}(r,d)} \twoheadrightarrow \mathcal{U}\) and the determinant
1915	    line bundle \(\det \mathcal{U}\) with its Pl\"ucker embedding.
1916	  \item \textbf{The functor-of-points representability} of \(\mathrm{Gr}(r,d)\)
1917	    -- that it represents \(\mathrm{Grass}(r,d) =
1918	    \Quot^{d,\mathcal{O}_{\mathbb{Z}}}_{\oplus^r \mathcal{O}_{\mathbb{Z}} /
1919	    \mathbb{Z} / \mathbb{Z}}\); this is blueprinted as
1920	    \cref{thm:grassmannian_representable} in
1921	    \cref{chap:Picard_QuotScheme}.
1922	  \item \textbf{The relative version over a general base \(S\)} with a locally
1923	    free sheaf \(V\) of rank \(r\): the scheme \(\mathrm{Gr}_S(V,d)\) obtained by
1924	    base change and gluing over a trivialising cover of \(V\). The
1925	    absolute-over-\(\mathbb{Z}\) construction of this chapter is the input to
1926	    that base change.
1927	\end{itemize}
